And here comes the moral

00:03:14.010 --> 00:03:17.270
dilemma.
Each Playstation 3 has a network card - in

00:03:17.270 --> 00:03:21.280
fact, two of them, Ethernet and
WiFi, which, like all other network devices,

00:03:21.280 --> 00:03:26.030
has a unique MAC-address. This
is exactly the address PSN uses to pick out

00:03:26.030 --> 00:03:30.870
and ban you device. The utility
allows to change the address to any other,

00:03:30.870 --> 00:03:35.540
the problem is, it has to be in
the PS3 range. Where you can get one? Well,

00:03:35.540 --> 00:03:40.140
I leave this up to you, just bear
in mind, that if two consoles with the same

00:03:40.140 --> 00:03:45.849
MAC-address get online simultaneously -
both users will get banned, that is you and

00:03:45.849 --> 00:03:49.590
the innocent other gamer whose
MAC address you are using.

00:03:49.590 --> 00:03:55.060
So, having two consoles - one with OFW, which
you use for online play,

00:03:55.060 --> 00:03:59.620
and the other with CFW for backups is the
best option for both XBOX Live

00:03:59.620 --> 00:04:00.569
and Playstation Network.

